 {"id":"franken_numpy-4oo7","title":"Allow non-finite tensorsolve/tensorinv parity","description":"`tensorsolve` and `tensorinv` still reject non-finite inputs up front, but NumPy forwards these through the underlying linear solve/inverse semantics.\n\nEvidence:\n- `np.linalg.tensorsolve([[inf,1,0],[0,3,1],[2,0,3]], [1,2,3]) -> [0, 0.33333333, 1]`\n- `np.linalg.tensorsolve([[nan,1,0],[0,3,1],[2,0,3]], [1,2,3]) -> [nan, 0.45454545, 0.63636364]`\n- `np.linalg.tensorinv` on 2D square input should mirror `inv_nxn` behavior for the same non-finite matrix.\n\nGoal: remove stale finite guards and add focused parity tests.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-01T18:35:45.878207431Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-01T18:37:55.245766780Z","closed_at":"2026-04-01T18:37:55.245496438Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
